\left(1-\dfrac{1}{n}\right)\ln{(1+\sqrt{2})}+\dfrac{\sqrt{2}}{2n}\le\sum_{k=1}^{n}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{n^2+k^2}}\le\ln{(1+\sqrt{2})}
\sum_{k=1}^{n}\dfrac{1}{n^2+k^2}=\sum_{k=1}^{n}\dfrac{1}{n\sqrt{1+\left(\dfrac{k}{n}\right)^2}}\le\int_{0}^{1}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1+x^2}}dx=\ln{(1+\sqrt{2})}
a=(n-1)/n
I(a)\geqslant a\ln{(1+\sqrt{2})}
x=at
1+a^2t^2\leqslant1+t^2
 \sum_{k=1}^{n-1}\dfrac1{\sqrt{n^2+k^2}}\geqslant I(a),\qquad I(a)=\int_{0}^{a}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1+x^2}}\mathrm dx, 
 I(a)=a\int_{0}^{1}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1+a^2t^2}}\mathrm dt\geqslant a\int_{0}^{1}\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1+t^2}}\mathrm dt, 
